{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_63","type":"agent_message","text":"The rerun exposed the real issue with my first condition choice: `typeReached` on the transaction config classes is too late, because Spring instantiates `OnClassCondition` before those types count as reached. The next patch will move those condition registrations to the earlier Spring parser/evaluator classes that are actually on the failing stack, and I’m also adding the newly revealed `.class` resources for the imported selector/registrar support types."}}
